# Agent Execution Rules

## Before Coding

The agent must understand:

- objective
- scope
- acceptance criteria
- architectural constraints
- expected files to change

## During Execution

- keep changes scoped
- prefer readability
- avoid hidden side effects
- preserve modularity
- preserve traceability

## Scraper Rules

- provider logic must remain isolated
- never mix business logic into scrapers
- preserve raw provider data
- use retries carefully
- assume layouts may break

## Backend Rules

- prefer explicit APIs
- avoid unnecessary abstractions
- preserve MVP simplicity
- use clear naming

## Documentation Rules

Update repository documentation when:

- architecture changes
- workflows change
- operational behavior changes
- contracts change

## Done Criteria

A task is only done when:

- implementation works
- ticket scope is respected
- documentation is updated if needed
- handoff exists
